One month ago, New Haven Firefighter, Ricardo Torres Jr, lost his life in the line of duty in my Connecticut hometown.  Tragically, he left behind his childhood sweetheart and pregnant wife, @errrcalynne, to raise their unborn son, Crew, and 1-year-old toddler, Oliver, without her rock & love of her life. 

Moments like this make many of us feel so helpless and insignificant, left only to pass along our condolences in person or on social media. 

So when the wife of New Haven’s Assistant Fire Chief and longtime friend, @colleendelaney_ called me to say that Ricardo’s widow was a HUGE fan of the @realhousewivesfranchise & that she and her husband, @jmcca1, wanted to put together a special video tribute to lift his widow spirits, it was my honor to leap into action and help make it happen.

I cannot thank @mrsjillzarin & @teresagiudice enough for immediately mobilizing their powerful connections on behalf of this incredible family.  You are two of the most altruistic & compassionate human beings I’ve ever met & it’s an honor to call you both friends. 🥰 

I am officially newfound fans of EVERY SINGLE HOUSEWIFE who took the time to send their love & support to Erica, Oliver, Crew and the entire @newhavenfireservice. 

Thank you for making Erica’s TODAY better than her YESTERDAY.

We love you @lisavanderpump @dorindamedley @jackiegoldschneider @therealmargaretjosephs @countessluann!!! 🇺🇸🚒👩‍🚒❤️🙏🏽
